1. Start a new document, problemset3.Rmd, in your soc10problemsets repository. (You can download a template [here](https://github.com/Soc10Spring2026/soc10problemsets_templates), but be sure to save it in your own soc10problemsets repo). Change your name in the header. Load the `gapminder` data using `library(gapminder)`. Create a simple plot with two of the variables. __Commit__ your changes. 

Here I created a scatter plot that illustrates life expectancy across continents. Meaning, the x axis is the regions and y axis is the average life expectancy for each country. Each dot depicts a country during a specific year. 

```{r q1, echo = TRUE}

library(gapminder)
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(data = gapminder, 
            mapping = aes(x = continent, y = lifeExp))+
  geom_point()

```

2. Now, modify your plot! For each change that you make, explain your decision, in terms of the visual elements. __Commit__ your changes. 

Now for question 2 looking at quesiton one made it hard to understand what the data was showing me, so to make it more clear I made a few changes. First, I created a boxplot to show the median and range of life expectancy. I then made the box plot balck so it would be easy to compare with each country clearly where the range of life expectancy was. I also added jittered points which means that it spreads the points out to prevent them from being as cluttered and overlapping as they were in question 1. Next, I added color to make it easy to diffrenciate each country from one another. After doing this, I then assigned each country a color to make it easy to draw compairisons. Lastly, I improved the labels and gave it a title, x and y axis to help the reader to know how to interpret this data visual. 

```{r q2, echo = TRUE}

ggplot(gapminder, 
      mapping = aes(x = continent, y = lifeExp, col = continent))+
geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.5)+
geom_jitter(alpha = 0.3, width = 0.3)+
scale_color_manual(values = c("red", "pink", "orange", "green", "blue))+
scale_size_continuous(range = c(0.5, 6))+ 
labs(title = "Life Expectancy by Continent",
x = "Continent",
y = "Life Expectancy",
col = "Continent")

```

